the bill frisell 858 quartet events at stanford the bill frisell 858 quartet facebook twitter email print add to calendar bill frisell's sound is instantly identifiable yet defies description named for a series of paintings by gerhard richter the 858 quartet includes violinist and sjw alum jenny scheinman violist eyvind kang and cellist hank roberts together they are likely to take improvisatory flights that touch on styles and idioms that are seemingly diverse and eclectic but united by the vitality of their roots the observer describes him this way the brilliant guitarist embraces a jazzy kind of post rock multi textured multi hued that never sees frisell sacrifice his impeccable technique or neglect the deep structure of his songs but never sees him forget to have fun either though frisell has been turning the jazz world on its ear for more than 20 years this is his first sjf appearance when sunday july 31 2011 8 00 pm approximate duration of 2 hour s where dinkelspiel auditorium 471 lagunita dr stanford ca 94305 map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags performance music arts sponsor stanford jazz workshop contact 736 0324 info stanfordjazz org admission tickets $36 general $22 students stanford ticket office 650 725 arts 2787 http tickets stanford edu permalink http events stanford edu events 279 27991 more info last modified july 26 2011
